g.text: History of SSPX and Marcel Lefebvre Relations with the Vatican (1970-2026)
Public statement questioning validity of Vatican II
June 9, 1988: Orders him NOT to proceed
Shows attending SSPX Mass ≠ automatic schism
2000: Large pilgrimage to Rome for Jubilee
1. Permission for all priests to celebrate Tridentine Mass
but SSPX still lacks canonical status
and bishops have no canonical function
- Must accept Vatican II & subsequent teaching
2009: Gives CDF task of dialogue with SSPX
little change, objects to JP2 beatiﬁcation
as insuﬃcient to overcome doctrinal problems
Mar 16, 2012: Invited to clarify by Apr 15
Oct 27, 2012: PCED notes SSPX needs more time
Dec 2012: Letter from Abp. Di Noia (VP PCED)
Vatican II texts themselves are the problem,
notes Francis read Lefebvre biography twice,
tolerant view of SSPX in Argentina
Dec 2015: Grants faculties for SSPX priests
Dies at 07:35 UTC+2 on Easter Monday
at 07:35 local time on Easter Monday

Not in full communion, but not formal schism
Has limited faculties for confession & marriage
